To construct our desired neighborhood $u$ in $H^n$, we can take the preimage $f^{-1}(v)$, which is an open subset of $\mathbb{R}^n$. Since $f$ is a diffeomorphism, $f^{-1}(v)$ is open in $\mathbb{R}^n$, and thus also in $H^n$ (since $H^n$ is a subspace of $\mathbb{R}^n$). 

So, our neighborhood $u$ in $H^n$ will be $f^{-1}(v)$, which is open in $H^n$, contains the point corresponding to $x$ (which is $f^{-1}(x)$), and is diffeomorphic to $v$ (via the inverse of $f$). 

